# AWS CloudFront Fundamentals

## What CloudFront Is

Amazon CloudFront is a Content Delivery Network (CDN) that delivers content with low latency using edge locations distributed around the world.

## Why CloudFront Matters

CloudFront improves performance, reduces latency, and adds security layers in front of applications and static websites.

---

# Core Concepts

## Distributions

- Main CloudFront configuration resource
- Defines origins, behaviors, and caching settings

## Origins

- Source of the content served by CloudFront
- Can be S3 buckets, EC2 instances, or load balancers

## Edge Locations

- Global locations that cache content closer to users
- Reduce response time and improve availability

## Caching

- Stores content temporarily at edge locations
- Reduces requests to the origin and improves performance

